oofem.out
2D linear mass-transport on 100x100 mm rect with circular inclusions
nltransienttransportproblem nsteps 100 deltat 1.0 rtol 1.e-3 alpha 1. nsmax 200 nmodules 1
vtkxmllattice tstep_step 1 dofman_all primvars 1 5
domain 2dMassLatticeTransport
OutputManager tstep_all dofman_all
ncrosssect 0 nmat 2 nbc 1 nic 1 nltf 1 nset 1
# Linear (constant k, constant c) transport — `contype 0` is the default and
# `m` / `a` are not parsed in that branch. Diffusivity D = k / (vis · c).
# Matrix: D = 2e-5 m²/s → diffusion length sqrt(D · t) ≈ 45 mm over the
# 100 s run, so the front penetrates the bottom half of the specimen
# and threads visibly around the aggregates rather than blowing past
# them across the full height.
latticetransmat 1 d 1. k 2.e-5 vis 1. c 1. thetas 1. thetar 0.
# Aggregate: D = 2e-9 m²/s, 10 000× slower than matrix — diffusion length
# sqrt(D · t) ≈ 0.45 mm over the 100 s run stays well below the 2.5–6 mm
# aggregate radii, so each disk remains visibly dry throughout the
# simulation and the wetting front gets clearly deflected around them.
latticetransmat 2 d 1. k 2.e-9 vis 1. c 1. thetas 1. thetar 0.
# Saturated bottom (prescribed pressure = 1); rest of the specimen starts at 0
# via the initial condition. Linear problem — Picard converges in 1 iter/step
# so no BC ramping needed.
BoundaryCondition 1 loadTimeFunction 1 prescribedvalue 1.
InitialCondition 1 Conditions 1 u 0. dofs 1 11 set 1
ConstantFunction 1 f(t) 1.
Set 1 allelements
#@grid 2dTM
#@mesher qhull
#@diam 0.002
#@perflag 2 0 0
#@thickness 1.0
#@lumpedcapacity 1
#@rect 1 box 4 0. 0. 0.1 0.1
# Any element with at least one endpoint in an aggregate disk takes the
# low-permeability aggregate material (mat 2) — both `inside` (both ends
# in) and `interface` (one in, one out) route to mat 2. Edges with both
# endpoints in the matrix keep the default mat 1.
#@inclusionfile packing.dat itz 1.e-4 inside 2 interface 2
#@nodebc 1 face 2 min
